There is a potential call to a disposed viewer here.

LabelUpdateJob has the following code:

if (canUpdateViewer()) {
	StructuredViewer tree = getViewer();
	tree.update(updates, null);
}

If the viewer is disposed between canUpdateViewer() and tree.update() you 
could be talking to disposed widgets. As this code is run in an asyncExec you 
can be affected by a context switch.

handleDispose(DisposeEvent event) is defined in ContentViewer. You would be 
better off to try and use this method to clear out the viewer reference.
